This paper is about generating natural language descriptions from structured data, which is a common task in natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also proposes a novel seq2seq architecture with attention mechanisms, which involves machine learning techniques, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) another likely category. The paper also evaluates its model on a large dataset, which suggests cs.LG (Machine Learning) as another possible category. Additionally, the paper involves information retrieval techniques to encode the content and structure of a table, which suggests cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as another possible category. Finally, the paper uses a dual attention mechanism, which involves neural networks, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) another possible category.
